Man, you must be exhausted from the drive.

01:35:05.820 --> 01:35:08.540
Why don't you let us make you a cup of tea?

01:35:08.540 --> 01:35:12.860
Thanks, but I'd better be going.

01:35:12.860 --> 01:35:15.020
Thanks for the invitation.

01:35:15.100 --> 01:35:18.180
Say, we had to run off.

01:35:18.180 --> 01:35:20.540
Yes, well, they never do stay long anyway.

01:35:20.540 --> 01:35:24.300
The main thing is we have our little Charlie with us.

01:35:24.300 --> 01:35:28.220
Let us give you the grand tour of our humble abode.

01:35:28.220 --> 01:35:51.180
Pretty comfortable.

01:35:51.180 --> 01:35:52.340
Oh, I'm sure we'll be fine.

01:35:52.340 --> 01:35:54.780
No, no.

01:35:54.780 --> 01:35:59.340
We're only trying to be good hosts.

01:35:59.340 --> 01:36:04.220
Madeleine, I thought we agreed not to mention that.

01:36:04.260 --> 01:36:09.140
Brevidia, I only said hosts, not ghosts.

01:36:09.140 --> 01:36:10.900
Ghosts?

01:36:10.900 --> 01:36:11.980
Silly me.

01:36:11.980 --> 01:36:26.620
My hearing isn't about it used to be.

01:36:26.620 --> 01:36:30.470
Your aunts are totally neat.

01:36:30.470 --> 01:36:33.110
What?

01:36:33.110 --> 01:36:34.470
Weird.

01:36:34.470 --> 01:36:37.070
Why, because their house isn't new and perfect like yours?

01:36:37.070 --> 01:36:39.670
We can't all be rich and rich.

01:36:39.670 --> 01:36:42.350
Hey, don't look at him wrinkly.

01:36:42.350 --> 01:36:47.720
Fine, do it yourself if you're going to be picky.

01:36:47.720 --> 01:36:51.640
Mom said I have to take care of my things.

01:36:51.640 --> 01:36:53.760
Whatever, I'll draw your bath sire.

01:36:53.760 --> 01:37:11.270
Hey, wait, a voice from outside.

01:37:11.270 --> 01:37:12.310
The wind, Charles.

01:37:12.310 --> 01:37:13.390
You heard the wind.

01:37:13.390 --> 01:38:23.380
Now get a move on or you'll be late for supper.

01:38:23.380 --> 01:38:26.420
This old thing never quite works right, I'm afraid.

01:38:26.420 --> 01:38:29.300
We're only using it because the electric range doesn't

01:38:29.300 --> 01:38:31.220
work when the power's out.

01:38:31.220 --> 01:38:32.860
Why is the power out?

01:38:32.860 --> 01:38:35.420
Oh, it's that old electric company.

01:38:35.420 --> 01:38:36.940
They get all op-ed even a person just

01:38:36.940 --> 01:38:38.860
to weave it late with the payment.

01:38:38.860 --> 01:38:42.580
Gratidia, it's been three months.

01:38:42.580 --> 01:38:44.100
Push, Madine.

01:38:44.100 --> 01:38:45.820
Remember what father always said,

01:38:45.820 --> 01:38:47.900
keep your finances to yourself.

01:38:47.900 --> 01:38:49.620
Gee, if you're having trouble with money,

01:38:49.620 --> 01:38:52.860
well, won't Charles' parents help you out?

01:38:52.860 --> 01:38:55.780
Neither a borrower nor a lender be.

01:38:55.780 --> 01:38:58.580
The father say that, too, Greta.

01:38:58.580 --> 01:39:01.420
Actually, father would roll over in his grave

01:39:01.420 --> 01:39:04.700
if he heard us even talking about borrowing money

01:39:04.700 --> 01:39:07.700
from the Pemberton and Schilling side of the family.

01:39:07.700 --> 01:39:10.940
Why, I mean, it's not like they're short on cash.

01:39:10.980 --> 01:39:12.780
It was this little feud.

01:39:12.780 --> 01:39:14.780
It was a long time ago.

01:39:14.780 --> 01:39:19.620
There was a terrible falling out between father and Uncle Charlie.

01:39:19.620 --> 01:39:22.420
Uncle Charlie was Charles' great-grandfather.

01:39:22.420 --> 01:39:25.740
He hired a common criminal to work on the farm.

01:39:25.740 --> 01:39:28.220
Maylene, Uncle Charlie didn't know he was a criminal

01:39:28.220 --> 01:39:29.100
when he hired him.

01:39:29.100 --> 01:39:32.860
Yes, but father thought there was something odd about him

01:39:32.860 --> 01:39:36.860
from the start who Uncle Charlie wouldn't listen.

01:39:36.860 --> 01:39:38.700
Wow, was he a murderer?

01:39:38.700 --> 01:39:40.060
Goodness, no.

01:39:40.060 --> 01:39:42.700
Far as I know, he was a bank robber.

01:39:42.700 --> 01:39:43.780
Well, what happened?

01:39:43.780 --> 01:39:45.900
The police caught him in the woods out back

01:39:45.900 --> 01:39:47.660
and put him on the train to prison.

01:39:47.660 --> 01:39:49.020
End of story.

01:39:49.020 --> 01:39:53.260
The Greta dear, that wasn't my understanding.

01:39:53.260 --> 01:39:55.660
I heard he never made it to prison.

01:39:55.660 --> 01:40:01.760
Everybody on it was killed.

01:40:01.760 --> 01:40:04.240
They never found the body of that.

01:40:04.240 --> 01:40:44.010
Close that window after we left the smoke out.

01:40:44.010 --> 01:40:45.810
We did, sister.

01:40:45.850 --> 01:40:48.730
Maybe it doesn't shut just right.

01:40:48.730 --> 01:40:52.850
I'm sure I felt a distinct chill just now.

01:40:52.850 --> 01:40:55.050
It's all right, children.

01:40:55.050 --> 01:40:57.650
We'll see about having it fixed in the morning.

01:40:57.650 --> 01:41:02.250
Walter was supposed to do it, but he left rather suddenly.

01:41:02.250 --> 01:41:03.770
Who's Walter?

01:41:03.770 --> 01:41:05.970
He was our old maintenance man.

01:41:05.970 --> 01:41:08.850
I'm afraid he got rather impatient with us.

01:41:08.850 --> 01:41:10.210
Because he couldn't pay him?

01:41:10.210 --> 01:41:12.210
Is that why he left, Greta?

01:41:12.210 --> 01:41:14.290
I thought it was because of the ghost.

01:41:14.290 --> 01:41:15.210
Ghost?

01:41:15.210 --> 01:41:16.610
You like some more macaroni and cheese.

01:41:16.610 --> 01:41:17.810
There's lots.

01:41:17.810 --> 01:41:19.250
You think there's a ghost here?

01:41:19.250 --> 01:41:20.490
Who is it, the bank robber?

01:41:20.490 --> 01:41:21.610
Ghost?

01:41:21.610 --> 01:41:24.410
I don't think we should talk about such things.

01:41:24.410 --> 01:41:25.290
Why not?

01:41:25.290 --> 01:41:27.290
Because we know how young imaginations

01:41:27.290 --> 01:41:29.730
can take the simplest things and build them up

01:41:29.730 --> 01:41:31.810
into nightmares and the like.

01:41:31.810 --> 01:41:33.730
But I'm not afraid of ghosts, and neither is Charles.

01:41:33.730 --> 01:41:35.770
Are you, Charles?

01:41:35.770 --> 01:41:37.530
Ghosts?

01:41:37.530 --> 01:41:39.570
Really, dear, it's better we don't.

01:41:39.570 --> 01:41:41.730
I'm going to apologize, because every time I

01:41:41.730 --> 01:41:44.730
talk about this, strange things happen.

01:41:44.730 --> 01:41:47.730
Maylene, that is enough.

01:42:14.290 --> 01:42:50.900
Give that back to me.

01:42:50.900 --> 01:42:53.980
The Secret Society and their special guest star

01:42:53.980 --> 01:42:55.180
will be right back.

01:42:55.180 --> 01:42:57.980
Happy Snick-a-versary.

01:42:57.980 --> 01:43:00.540
Ah, to get inside this box of lucky charms,

01:43:00.540 --> 01:43:02.900
rainbow magic is what it takes for a close look

01:43:02.900 --> 01:43:04.340
at me marshmallow shapes.

01:43:04.340 --> 01:43:05.820
Hey, a box of lucky charms.

01:43:05.820 --> 01:43:07.260
And no sign of life.

01:43:07.260 --> 01:43:08.580
With no pickles.

01:43:08.580 --> 01:43:09.580
Sure.

01:43:09.580 --> 01:43:11.380
Yeah.

01:43:11.380 --> 01:43:14.300
Now at Burger King, you can collect Save the Animal Cards.

01:43:14.300 --> 01:43:18.260
You can save mammals, fish, birds, and red cows, and amphibians.

01:43:18.260 --> 01:43:21.340
There's 17 cards and four albums, one with every kid's meal.

01:43:21.340 --> 01:43:24.420
You can save them in albums.

01:43:24.420 --> 01:43:26.380
Or treat them with friends.

01:43:26.380 --> 01:43:29.180
You'll all die for my life at Burger King now.

01:43:29.180 --> 01:43:34.720
I'm with Zelda from the very start.

01:43:34.720 --> 01:43:36.720
I got the heart and smarts to play the part.

01:43:36.720 --> 01:43:38.720
But to down with Zelda.

01:43:38.720 --> 01:43:41.600
To creep it through within our head view.

01:43:41.600 --> 01:43:44.040
Because a man's got to do what a man's got to do.

01:43:44.040 --> 01:43:46.760
So I stay on track to collect the facts.

01:43:46.760 --> 01:43:47.840
Never cut to slack.

01:43:47.840 --> 01:43:49.680
And I always watch my back for jacks.

01:43:49.680 --> 01:43:51.680
To down with Zelda, yeah.

01:43:51.680 --> 01:43:54.000
As soon as then, I'm the man with the plan.

01:43:54.000 --> 01:43:55.280
Because the power's in my head.

01:43:55.280 --> 01:43:56.520
And the power's in my hands.

01:43:56.520 --> 01:44:00.490
To down with Zelda.

01:44:00.490 --> 01:44:04.170
Now back to the sneak-aversary, if you dare.

01:44:04.170 --> 01:44:34.610
What are you doing?

01:44:34.610 --> 01:44:35.650
Charles, you had a bad dream.

01:44:35.650 --> 01:44:37.490
Now get out of my bed and go back to sleep.

01:44:37.490 --> 01:44:38.290
It wasn't a dream.

01:44:38.290 --> 01:44:40.770
I mean, I was having a bad dream.

01:44:40.770 --> 01:44:41.970
And then I woke up.

01:44:41.970 --> 01:44:44.810
The window burst open, crashed like that.

01:44:44.810 --> 01:44:46.050
And then I looked down.

01:44:46.090 --> 01:44:47.370
I saw him.

01:44:47.370 --> 01:45:15.170
Oh, he's got to believe me.

01:45:15.170 --> 01:45:18.450
Now, children, it's not nice to argue.

01:45:18.450 --> 01:45:21.130
Why won't you tell Auntie Greta what's wrong?

01:45:21.130 --> 01:45:24.210
Charles kept me up all night because he thinks he saw a ghost.

01:45:24.210 --> 01:45:26.050
He's mad because I don't believe him.

01:45:26.050 --> 01:45:27.130
What's that?

01:45:27.130 --> 01:45:28.570
What did you see?

01:45:28.570 --> 01:45:29.370
The ghost.

01:45:29.370 --> 01:45:30.850
I saw it.

01:45:30.850 --> 01:45:32.170
He says it talked to him.

01:45:32.170 --> 01:45:34.410
It did.

01:45:34.410 --> 01:45:36.410
Greta, did you hear that?

01:45:36.410 --> 01:45:40.410
It's never spoken to us.

01:45:40.410 --> 01:45:42.290
You mean you've seen it, too?

01:45:42.290 --> 01:45:44.210
Now, Daphne and Debbie.

01:45:44.210 --> 01:45:47.770
Daphne, you mean there is a ghost,

01:45:47.770 --> 01:45:49.370
and it's not just a ghost story?

01:45:49.370 --> 01:45:52.010
Well, I suppose there's no use pretending now.

01:45:52.010 --> 01:45:55.330
It was little Charlie we were trying to protect.

01:45:55.330 --> 01:45:57.290
He's already seen it.

01:45:57.290 --> 01:45:59.690
Besides, it never comes into the house,

01:45:59.690 --> 01:46:01.650
so there's no need to worry.

01:46:01.650 --> 01:46:03.410
You guys really believe this, don't you?

01:46:03.410 --> 01:46:05.050
Of course we do.

01:46:05.050 --> 01:46:05.650
Cool.

01:46:05.650 --> 01:46:07.010
Well, whose ghost is it?

01:46:07.010 --> 01:46:09.530
Well, no one knows exactly, but there

01:46:09.570 --> 01:46:13.090
was this little boy who lived at a neighboring farm,

01:46:13.090 --> 01:46:16.530
and father said he used to come over here all the time,

01:46:16.530 --> 01:46:19.770
sneak around the house trying to find

01:46:19.770 --> 01:46:22.850
where Mother hid the cookies.

01:46:22.850 --> 01:46:24.050
What happened to him?

01:46:24.050 --> 01:46:25.130
It's very tragic.

01:46:25.130 --> 01:46:26.930
No one really knows.

01:46:26.930 --> 01:46:31.330
They just found him one day out in the woodshed,

01:46:31.330 --> 01:46:35.250
all curled up like he was trying to keep a warm.

01:46:35.250 --> 01:46:38.450
They said he froze to death for a thing.

01:46:38.490 --> 01:46:40.170
How sad.

01:46:40.170 --> 01:46:40.970
Look at that.

01:46:40.970 --> 01:46:44.070
I was gone out again.

01:46:44.070 --> 01:46:46.670
Oh, no, and we have no more wood.

01:46:46.670 --> 01:46:48.830
Does that mean we're going to freeze to death too?

01:46:48.830 --> 01:46:50.470
No, there's plenty of wood around.

01:46:50.470 --> 01:46:54.900
Just tell me where to go, and I'll bring some in.

01:46:54.900 --> 01:46:57.340
I was thinking, maybe we should go Mom and Dad,

01:46:57.340 --> 01:46:58.620
and they can come and get us.

01:46:58.620 --> 01:47:00.540
I'm sure their wedding's over by now.

01:47:00.540 --> 01:47:02.620
The axe isn't where they said it would be.

01:47:02.620 --> 01:47:03.580
Axe?

01:47:03.580 --> 01:47:05.300
How else do you chop wood?

01:47:05.300 --> 01:47:06.140
I don't know.

01:47:06.140 --> 01:47:07.300
I've never chopped wood.

01:47:07.300 --> 01:47:08.940
Well, there's a first time for everything.

01:47:08.940 --> 01:47:13.210
Come on.

01:47:13.210 --> 01:47:14.930
Chopping wood?

01:47:14.930 --> 01:47:29.870
It's filthy.

01:47:29.870 --> 01:47:33.380
This should do the trick.

01:47:33.380 --> 01:47:35.220
Hey, this isn't hard at all.

01:47:35.220 --> 01:47:36.380
In fact, it's kind of fun.

01:47:36.380 --> 01:47:37.300
Want to try?

01:47:37.300 --> 01:47:40.790
Yeah.

01:47:40.790 --> 01:47:43.470
I'm not allowed to play the sharp things.

01:47:43.470 --> 01:47:44.550
I can't take it anymore.

01:47:44.550 --> 01:47:46.390
You are a complete and total wuss.

01:47:46.390 --> 01:47:47.390
I am not.

01:47:47.390 --> 01:47:48.190
You are too.

01:47:48.190 --> 01:47:50.110
You're always finding an excuse not to do things.

01:47:50.110 --> 01:47:51.790
When are you going to quit being such a freak?

01:47:51.790 --> 01:47:53.270
I am not a freak.

01:47:53.270 --> 01:47:54.910
Yeah, right.

01:47:54.910 --> 01:47:57.070
If it weren't for me, you'd be a total couch potato

01:47:57.070 --> 01:47:59.110
sitting at home, playing a nice safe video game

01:47:59.110 --> 01:48:00.350
and your nice clean clothes.

01:48:00.350 --> 01:48:02.310
What's wrong with clean clothes?

01:48:02.310 --> 01:48:04.110
You want to know what's wrong with clean clothes?

01:48:04.110 --> 01:48:10.300
I'll show you what's wrong with clean clothes.

01:48:10.300 --> 01:48:11.940
Look, he's still alive.

01:48:11.940 --> 01:48:12.740
What a surprise.

01:48:12.740 --> 01:48:14.300
He survived a little bit of mud.

01:48:14.300 --> 01:48:14.780
That's him.

01:48:14.780 --> 01:48:17.100
I'm telling my mom you did that.

01:48:17.100 --> 01:48:26.080
I'm going to be angry.

01:48:26.080 --> 01:48:35.350
What was that?

01:48:35.350 --> 01:48:36.870
I think it came from over here.

01:48:36.870 --> 01:50:36.890
No.

01:50:36.890 --> 01:50:44.860
What does it want?

01:50:44.860 --> 01:50:47.100
What?

01:50:47.100 --> 01:50:49.640
He was in the law.

01:50:49.640 --> 01:50:53.510
The bad guy pulled up his-

01:50:53.510 --> 01:51:09.120
Charles, see something.

01:51:09.120 --> 01:51:59.180
What are you doing?

01:51:59.180 --> 01:52:02.630
The jacket.

01:52:02.630 --> 01:52:06.230
That V looks like some kind of key.

01:52:06.270 --> 01:52:14.730
I know for the stove pipe.

01:52:14.730 --> 01:52:16.530
That's why it never worked properly.

01:52:16.530 --> 01:52:32.460
We couldn't get the flue open without it.

01:52:32.460 --> 01:52:45.130
Greta, I have a feeling your money troubles are over.

01:52:45.130 --> 01:52:49.140
The criminal hid the gold in the pipe.

01:52:49.140 --> 01:52:51.860
Little boy saw him when he was looking for cookies.

01:52:51.860 --> 01:52:53.740
Charles' dream.

01:52:53.740 --> 01:52:54.860
Poor kid.

01:52:54.860 --> 01:52:59.740
He froze to death hiding from the criminal and no one knew.

01:52:59.740 --> 01:53:11.040
I told you you'd get the shivers.

01:53:11.040 --> 01:53:14.880
I declare this meaning of the Heat Wave Society.

01:53:14.880 --> 01:53:16.680
Close.

01:53:16.680 --> 01:54:57.500
Good night, everybody.

01:54:57.500 --> 01:54:58.540
Four of a kind.

01:54:58.540 --> 01:55:00.580
It's four reasons to stay at home.

01:55:00.580 --> 01:55:03.100
It's fortified with four essential episodes,

01:55:03.100 --> 01:55:05.420
the cream of the classic TV crop.

01:55:05.420 --> 01:55:07.580
It's very, very Nick at night.

01:55:07.580 --> 01:55:10.100
This week, it's very, very Alan Brady.

01:55:10.100 --> 01:55:11.980
He's everyone's favorite boss.

01:55:11.980 --> 01:55:12.980
War.

01:55:12.980 --> 01:55:16.300
We should encourage him and a humble genius.

01:55:16.300 --> 01:55:18.380
I don't owe anything to anybody.

01:55:18.380 --> 01:55:20.420
He's very, very Alan Brady.

01:55:20.420 --> 01:55:22.700
That's this week's very, very Nick at night.

01:55:22.700 --> 01:55:24.940
And it all starts tonight at 10, 9 central.

01:55:24.940 --> 01:55:26.180
Join us if you can.

01:55:26.180 --> 01:55:27.180
Thank you.

01:55:27.180 --> 01:55:30.060
He has no upper lip, like this.

01:55:30.060 --> 01:55:31.460
He shaves his entire body.

01:55:31.460 --> 01:55:32.580
His ears.

01:55:32.580 --> 01:55:35.140
He's got one of those unibrow's.

01:55:35.140 --> 01:55:35.740
I hate that.

01:55:35.740 --> 01:55:38.460
A remote control holder for my birthday.

01:55:38.460 --> 01:55:38.980
Thank you.

01:55:38.980 --> 01:55:40.740
He calls me amigo.

01:55:40.740 --> 01:55:42.220
He reads mercenary magazines.

01:55:42.220 --> 01:55:43.340
He waxes his chest.

01:55:43.340 --> 01:55:46.260
Dinosaur making is not legitimate profession at all.

01:55:46.260 --> 01:55:48.340
East pack, backpacks come with a lifetime

01:55:48.340 --> 01:55:50.580
guarantee against defects.

01:55:50.620 --> 01:55:52.980
If only the same could be said for boyfriends.

01:55:52.980 --> 01:55:54.740
He bites his toenails.

01:55:54.740 --> 01:55:57.670
Ugh.

01:55:57.670 --> 01:55:59.390
I asked my parents if I was going to Kellogg's Frosted

01:55:59.390 --> 01:56:01.750
Meats, and all of a sudden I'm so grown up.

01:56:01.750 --> 01:56:03.510
Oh, he's eating so sensibly.

01:56:03.510 --> 01:56:05.590
Well, he knows just how cool his stuff is.

01:56:05.590 --> 01:56:07.270
Just check out all that whole grain wheat.

01:56:07.270 --> 01:56:07.870
Whole grain wheat.

01:56:07.870 --> 01:56:08.950
They're very nutritious.

01:56:08.950 --> 01:56:11.110
He's definitely eating this frosted.

01:56:11.110 --> 01:56:11.870
It jams.

01:56:11.870 --> 01:56:14.390
This is what every child genius should eat.

01:56:14.390 --> 01:56:16.670
Kellogg's Frosted Meats tastes so good,

01:56:16.670 --> 01:56:18.350
who cares about anything else.

01:56:18.350 --> 01:56:20.470
Besides, it's part of this complete breakfast.

01:56:20.470 --> 01:56:22.110
He's probably downstairs right now,

01:56:22.110 --> 01:56:24.510
writing his dissertation on world peace.

01:56:24.510 --> 01:56:25.190
There you go.

01:56:25.190 --> 01:56:26.670
All right.

01:56:26.670 --> 01:56:28.670
Yeah.

